The popularity of coffee continued to grow throughout the 19th and 20th centuries, with coffee becoming an important part of daily life for many people around the world. Today, coffee is produced in over 60 countries, with the largest producers being Brazil, Vietnam, and Colombia.

There are many different types of coffee, each with its own unique flavor and brewing method. Some of the most popular types of coffee include espresso, cappuccino, latte, and Americano. Coffee can be brewed using a variety of methods, including drip, French press, and espresso.

